.TH SHOAL 1 "July 2026" "Shoal 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shoal \- run the Shoal language and interactive shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shoal
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ script
.IR args ...]
.br
.B shoal
.I command
.RI [ args ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shoal is a structured, typed shell language backed by a resident execution kernel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c , " \-\-command " SOURCE
Evaluate source and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-standalone
Use an embedded kernel.
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V , " \-\-version"
Print the version.
.SH COMMANDS
.BR kernel , fmt , doctor , lsp , mcp , completions , prompt .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shoal-kernel (1),
.BR shoal-history (1),
.BR shoal-secret (1),
.BR shoal-token (1)
